# Releases: Always Attach the APK

For **every** GitHub release in this repo (alpha, beta, production, or ad-hoc), **attach the installable Android APK** as a release asset. Do not publish a release with only source or notes—users must be able to download and install from the release page.

## APK paths (this project)

After building from `android/`:

| Build        | Output file |
|-------------|-------------|
| Debug       | `android/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/turnTable.debug.apk` |
| Release     | `android/app/build/outputs/apk/release/turnTable.release.apk` (requires release signing) |

Use **debug** for quick/prerelease drops if release signing is not configured; use **release** for store-quality signed builds.

## Checklist (before publishing any release)

1. `./gradlew assembleDebug` and/or `./gradlew assembleRelease` (from `android/`).
2. Confirm the APK exists at one of the paths above.
3. Create the tag/release and **upload the APK** (`gh release upload`, GitHub UI “Attach binaries”, or equivalent).
4. Optionally note the attached file name in release notes.

## Example (GitHub CLI)

```bash
cd android && ./gradlew assembleDebug
gh release create "v1.0.0-alpha1" \
  app/build/outputs/apk/debug/turnTable.debug.apk \
  --title "v1.0.0-alpha1" --notes "..." --prerelease
```

**Never** ship a release without at least one APK asset for this Android app.
